news.title: UPEIDA seeks Rs 486 crore for logistics clusters in three Uttar Pradesh districts
news.para: The authority is shaping up the corridor to attract global defence manufacturing companies. So far, a land bank has been aggregated across seven districts, and the procedure to allot the plots is also underway.

news.title: Pacific Group to develop 15 lakh sq ft mall, 130-key hotel in Jaipur
news.para: Pacific Group Managing Director Abhishek Bansal said, "We have a portfolio of nine shopping malls and now we are expanding in Jaipur, Rajasthan."

news.title: Gurugram civic body to clear six lakh MT of construction waste in three months
news.para: The initiative, for which tenders were floated on Saturday, involves a private contractor who will manage the entire waste and transport it to the Basai processing facility in three months.

news.title: Boy’s cricket complaint triggers biggest crackdown in Hyderabad's Raidurg
news.para: Hydraa officials promptly launched a field inspection near the dargah area in Raidurg, in Shaikpet mandal, and uncovered large-scale illegal occupation in survey no. 5/2.

news.title: Over 9,000 Pune residents sign petition to stop construction on city’s hills
news.para: It is expected to review the boundary lines of the Biodiversity Park reservation and hill top-hill slope zones while formulating development control regulations (DCR) in Pune and submit its recommendations by May 8.

news.title: Builder directed to pay homebuyer near Coimbatore for poor construction quality
news.para: The commission -- comprising its president R Thangavel and members P Marimuthu and G Suguna -- has directed the builder to pay ₹50,000 as compensation to the buyer for the mental agony caused due to deficiency in service and ₹5,000 as the cost of the proceedings.

news.title: Action ordered against 58 sand depots; policy on M-sand in offing: Maharashtra revenue minister
news.para: The errant depots, to which notices were issued following reports of irregularities, included all 57 government-recognised ones, he told reporters.

news.title: Oberoi Realty's sales bookings rise 31% to Rs 5,266 crore in FY25
news.para: In a regulatory filing, Oberoi Realty informed that it has sold 928 units in 2024-25, as against 705 units in the preceding fiscal.

news.title: Chandigarh administration plans to demolish two colonies to make city slum free
news.para: "Plans are afoot for the demolition of Sanjay Colony and Janta Colony. Sanjay Colony is spread over 6 acres, and Janta Colony over 10 acres. Sanjay Colony is planned to be first vacated and then demolished by the end of this month," said a UT official.

news.title: Telangana government plans IT knowledge hub on 450 acres in Puppalaguda
news.para: ​The 450 acres earmarked for the hub includes nearly 200 acres provided earlier to housing societies by previous govts and another 250 acres abutting it that belongs to the Telangana Industrial Infrastructure Corporation (TGIIC).

news.title: Action will be taken against officials involved in illegal sand trade: Bihar deputy CM
news.para: Sinha's directive has come in the backdrop of large-scale illegal sand mining, transportation and storage by the agencies in the Aurangabad district.

news.title: Sand mining rampant off Yamuna, but on Delhi’s side: Ghaziabad DM
news.para: According to the report submitted at the NGT on Wednesday, the authorities had discovered an illegal embankment in Loni's Pachaiyra, Khand-2, which was promptly dismantled. Sandbags placed in the riverbed to facilitate sand excavation were also removed from the spot.

news.title: Pune Cantonment Board proposes two FSI for civil areas
news.para: The board submitted its proposal to the Principal Directorate of Defence Estates (PDDE) of Southern Command for consideration before sending it to the Directorate General of Defence Estates in New Delhi for a final approval.

news.title: Gujarat CM hints at faster building plan approval process
news.para: The CM said, "The Prime Minister has always emphasised ease of doing business. We are considering a system that allows plan approvals anytime — but without compromising on compliance."

news.title: Flat owners’ body in Ghaziabad seeks more power to hold RWA polls, address disputes
news.para: Federation representatives put forth several civic and environmental concerns, called for a formal role in overseeing housing society governance and highlighted the need for decentralised and citizen-led solutions to improve urban living.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body offers 5% property tax rebate till April 30
news.para: ​This comes on the heels of a relatively successful year for BBMP in 2024–25, during which it collected Rs 4,930 crore in property tax, an increase of about 25% over the previous year's collection of Rs 3,918 crore.

news.title: ED attaches Dalmia Cements (Bharat) owned land worth ₹377.2 crore
news.para: However, Dalmia Cements (Bharat) stated that the attached property is worth 793.3 crore. The attachment comes 14 years after the case was booked.

news.title: TNUHDB imposes fine on contractor for delayed projects in Chennai
news.para: Each of these projects, involving the construction of tenements using pre-fabricated concrete technology, was awarded on a turnkey basis with a stipulated completion period of 18 months from the date of site handover.

news.title: Bombay HC directs Neelkamal Realtors to finish & hand over eight buildings to MMRDA
news.para: The builder, Neelkamal Realtors Suburban Pvt Ltd, challenged a March 2022 rejection by the Mira Bhayandar Municipal Corporation (MBMC) of its request to switch to a new scheme under the new Unified Development Control and Promotion Regulations.
